/-!
# Actual-qlog eventual-tail reduction

The previous actual-qlog route asks for endpoint geometry data for every finite
shift of the one-over-pi denominator-log sequence.  The final construction only
uses one sufficiently far tail: far enough for positivity, the ratio cap, and
the endpoint geometry/counting estimates.
